JOHANNESBURG - South Africa take on India in a must-win ICC Champions Trophy encounter at The Oval, London on Sunday.India won the toss and elected to bowl in their group match against the Proteas. South Africa have made one change from their defeat against Pakistan. Andile Phehlukwayo comes for Wayne Parnell. Match PermutationsThe Proteas will have to overcome India to safely secure a semi-final berth in the competition.If both the India-SA and Pakistan-Sri Lanka fixtures are washed out, the Proteas will secure qualification with the Indians, due to a superior net run rate.On the flip side of the coin, if the India-SA engagement is washed out, but the Sri Lanka-Pakistan match goes on without wet weather interruption, the South Africans will be on the plane home. India have won the toss and will bowl first. "I'm pretty happy batting first... Pretty excited setting a good total today." - AB #ProteaFire pic.twitter.com/BKJKudVwQT IND XI: RG Sharma, S Dhawan, V Kohli, Y Singh, MS Dhoni, H Pandya, K Jadhav, R Jadeja, R Ashwin, B Kumar, J Bumrah Tweets about #INDvSA AND (FROM: @OfficialCSA since:2017-06-11 until:2017-06-12) eNCA